Email-to-Case Threading Limitations & Considerations

Required Editions:
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions

General Considerations
If you set up more than one email routing address, ask customers to email only one address at a time.

When two cases are merged, all additional incoming emails are associated with the parent case.
Ref ID-Based Threading:
Responses to case email alerts aren’t added to the case feed if Lightning threading or email header-based threading isn't enabled.
Incoming email responses missing a Ref ID create a new case instead of adding to an existing one.

Email Header-Based Threading
Enabled in Winter '23 and later, this adds replies to the alert to the case feed. In pre-Winter '23 orgs, incoming responses to the alert aren’t added if sent before enabling.
Lightning Threading
Inserting the Case Thread Token merge field into an email subject or body can cause new cases to be created if tokens are removed by modifying the email subject.

Alternatives to Lightning Threading:
The Messaging.InboundEmailHandler Apex interface lets you further customize email matching, but we don’t recommend this approach.
title: Email-to-Case Threading Limitations & Considerations
